  => structural fact, asserted by core_test::AXIS_COUNT/PAIR_COUNT/GENOME_BYTES triple
  |> airgenome/core/core.hexa:16 + archive/v1/docs/gates.hexa:20

@C AIRGENOME_GENOME_LAYOUT_V1_4 = canonical: 15 pairs × 4 bytes = 60 B (each pair = f32 little-endian IEEE-754). Hex encoding = 120 hex chars. Pair ordering = lex on (Axis,Axis). Source: archive/v1/docs/gates.hexa §"GENOME SERIALIZATION" + spec §"GateGenome 60-byte struct". :: omega_cycle_airgenome [10*]
  => fully-specified canonical layout (FROZEN in v1)
  |> airgenome/archive/v1/docs/gates.hexa lines 1138-1146

@C AIRGENOME_GENOME_LAYOUT_V1B_5 = alternate v1 layout (singularity-breakthrough plan, src/gates/genome.rs target): axes[0..24]=6×f32 + firing_bits[24..26]=u16 + pad[26..28] + ts[28..32]=u32 + counters[32..44]=3×f32 (procs/rss_mb/cpu_pct) + stats[44..60]=4×f32 (min/max/mean/stddev). Both add to 60 B exactly. :: omega_cycle_airgenome [10*]
  => alternate fully-specified layout (semantic dual of pairs-only)
  |> airgenome/archive/v1/docs/superpowers/plans/2026-04-05-gate-mesh-singularity-breakthrough.md lines 48-120

@C AIRGENOME_GENOME_LAYOUT_V2_6 = rebuild-v2 logical layout (modules/harvest.hexa lines 9-13): header pid(4)+ts(8)=12 B, vitals f32[6]=24 B, ema f32[6]=24 B → 60 B. JSONL serialized in forge/genomes.ring. axes 2/3/5 (gpu/npu/io) zero-filled in Mac path; axis 4 (power) sampled via top -l 2. :: omega_cycle_airgenome [10*]
  => fully-specified active-runtime layout
  |> airgenome/modules/harvest.hexa lines 1-25

@C AIRGENOME_BANACH_CEILING_7 = SINGULARITY = comptime { 2.0 / 3.0 } annotated "Banach 1/3 work ceiling" in archive/v1/docs/gates.hexa:21 — system can do at most 2/3 of theoretical max work, leaving 1/3 reserve. is_crossed(adjusted) := adjusted > SINGULARITY. :: omega_cycle_airgenome [10*]
  => named constant, file-pinned
  |> airgenome/archive/v1/docs/gates.hexa:21,228

@C AIRGENOME_BANACH_INTERPRETATION_8 = the "1/3 fixed point" framing reads as: contraction factor 1/3 ↔ 1 - 2/3 ceiling. Closure formula 1/(n(n-1)) with n=6 → 1/30 = 0.0333 = remaining gap from baseline 0.636 to 2/3 = 0.667. No formal Banach contraction proof in repo — phrase is heuristic anchor on the n=6 constant pack. :: omega_cycle_airgenome [7]
  => candidate (mathematical naming, not theorem-proved in this codebase)
