@C AIRGENOME_N6_CONSTANT_PACK_11 = inherited from nexus hexa-lang BT series (gates.hexa:14-32): TAU_PHI=6 (BT-344 τ+φ=n=6), SIGMA_J2=288 (BT-346 σ·J₂=288 fixed-point floor), BREAKTHROUGH_PERTURB=2401=7^4 (BT-345). Per-n=6 number theory: σ(6)=12, φ(6)=2, τ(6)=4, sopfr(6)=5, J₂(6)=24. PHI_TOLERANCE_N6=1/288=0.00347, PHI_THETA_N6=1/(σ-φ)=0.1. :: omega_cycle_airgenome [10*]
  => structural fact (number-theoretic anchors compile-time)
  |> airgenome/archive/v1/docs/gates.hexa lines 14-32

@C AIRGENOME_60_AS_PAIRS_TIMES_4_12 = 60 = PAIR_COUNT × 4 = C(6,2) × sizeof(f32). Note: 60 = 6·10 trivially, but the load-bearing factorization is C(6,2)·4 — pairs are first-class, axes second. (60 = J₂(6)·sopfr(6)/φ(6)/2 = 24·5/2 also fits but is not asserted in the repo.) :: omega_cycle_airgenome [10*]
  => structural fact (pair-centric, not axis-centric)
  |> airgenome/archive/v1/docs/gates.hexa:20 ("15 pairs × 4 bytes")

@C AIRGENOME_BREAKTHROUGH_FORMULA_13 = compute_adjusted(per_gate_mi, cross_gate_mi) = RAW + CURRENT_MESH + new_cross_coupling + new_mi_recovery + GHOST_PENALTY where RAW=0.6360, CURRENT_MESH=0.0044, GHOST_PENALTY=-0.0026, SCALE=0.0151/1.500. Pure-fn, deterministic. :: omega_cycle_airgenome [10*]
  => structural fact (the actual ascent function)
  |> airgenome/archive/v1/docs/gates.hexa lines 172-226

